Gafisa, Lojas Renner, Hypermarcas: Latin America Equity Preview

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-09-19T05:47:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/gafisa-lojas-renner-hypermarcas-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The MSCI Latin America Index rose 0.8 percent to 3,824.06.
Chilean markets will be closed today for a holiday.  Brazil   Anhanguera Educacional Participacoes SA (AEDU3)  (AEDU3 BS):
Brazil’s largest education company by market value agreed to buy
three rivals for 510.6 million reais ($294.6 million) as it taps
into Brazil’s fast-growing education sector. The shares dropped
1.9 percent to 24.82 reais.  Retailers and homebuilders may be active on inflation
reports from the Fundacao Instituto de Pesquisas Economicas and
the Getulio Vargas Foundation, to be released before the market
opens.  Gafisa SA (GFSA3)  (GFSA3 BS), Brazil’s third-biggest homebuilder
by revenue, advanced 0.8 percent to 7.21 reais. Lojas Renner SA
(LREN3 BS), Brazil’s biggest publicly traded clothing retailer,
added 1.8 percent to 56.99 reais.  Hypermarcas SA (HYPE3)  (HYPE3 BS),
Brazil’s fifth-largest consumer-goods company by market value,
slipped 0.8 percent to 11.97 reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
